---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="TripSharing · Support">
  <main class="support">
    <header class="page-header">
      <a class="back" href="/">← thehoodiethathoodies</a>
      <h1>TripSharing</h1>
      <p class="kicker">Support</p>
    </header>

    <article>
      <p class="lede">
        TripSharing is a group-trip expense app — Splitwise-style balances, with a
        one-tap "Open Venmo" handoff for actually settling up. This page is here to
        help if anything goes sideways.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to reach us is email. We read every message and reply within
        a couple of days, usually sooner.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:matthewzhenghi@gmail.com?subject=TripSharing%20support"
          >matthewzhenghi@gmail.com</a
        >
      </p>
      <p>When you write in, it helps to include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your device and iOS version (e.g. iPhone 14, iOS 18.2).</li>
        <li>The app version, shown at the bottom of the Settings screen.</li>
        <li>The display name or email you signed in with.</li>
        <li>The trip name and (if relevant) the 8-character invite code.</li>
        <li>A short description of what happened and what you expected.</li>
        <li>A screenshot if the issue is visual.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common questions</h2>

      <h3>I invited someone but they don't show up in Members on my phone.</h3>
      <p>
        Pull-to-refresh on the Members screen, or navigate out of the trip and back
        in — that re-fetches the latest member list. If they're still missing, ask
        them to double-check the 8-character invite code (it avoids 0/O and 1/I/L,
        so the only valid characters are A–Z and 2–9). Codes are case-insensitive.
      </p>

      <h3>The balance looks wrong.</h3>
      <p>
        TripSharing computes balances as <em>sum paid − sum owed</em> across every
        expense in the trip. Open the expense list and check that each row's amount,
        payer, and "split among" are correct. Tap an expense to edit it. If the
        numbers still don't add up, email us with the trip invite code and we'll
        take a look.
      </p>

      <h3>"Open Venmo" didn't open Venmo / opened the wrong account.</h3>
      <p>
        TripSharing launches Venmo via a deep link with the amount prefilled — it
        never sees your Venmo credentials, and it can't change which Venmo account
        you're signed into. Make sure the Venmo app is installed and that you're
        signed in to the right account inside Venmo. The other person's Venmo
        handle comes from <em>their</em> Settings screen — if it's wrong, ask them
        to update it.
      </p>

      <h3>I added an expense in the wrong currency.</h3>
      <p>
        Tap the expense to edit it. Currency is set per expense, not per trip, so
        you can fix it without touching the rest of the trip. The trip's default
        currency just pre-fills new expenses.
      </p>

      <h3>I want to leave a trip.</h3>
      <p>
        Open the trip → Members → tap your own row → Leave Trip. Your splits stay
        on existing expenses (so other members' balances don't silently shift), but
        you won't be added to new ones.
      </p>

      <h3>I'm the trip owner — how do I delete the trip?</h3>
      <p>
        Open the trip → tap the trash icon in the top right → confirm. This is
        permanent and removes every expense, split, and member record for that
        trip.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I change my display name or Venmo handle?</h3>
      <p>
        Settings → tap the field → edit → save. The "Saved" banner confirms the
        change and dismisses itself.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I sign out or switch accounts?</h3>
      <p>
        Settings → Sign out. The next launch returns you to the sign-in screen,
        where you can use Apple, Google, or email.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
      <p>
        Email us at
        <a href="mailto:matthewzhenghi@gmail.com?subject=TripSharing%20account%20deletion"
          >matthewzhenghi@gmail.com</a
        > with the subject "account deletion". We'll confirm and remove your
        profile within 30 days. Note that if you're a member of trips with other
        people, the trips themselves stay (so your travel companions' balances
        don't get corrupted) but your profile and identifying info are removed.
      </p>

      <h3>I forgot my password.</h3>
      <p>
        On the sign-in screen, tap "Forgot password?". Enter your email and we'll
        send a reset link. (If you originally signed in with Apple or Google, you
        don't have a password — just use that same provider again.)
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        For details on what data the app handles and why, see the
        <a href="/privacy/trip-sharing">TripSharing privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Other apps</h2>
      <p>
        Need help with Daily Math Friends instead? See the
        <a href="/dailymath">Daily Math Friends support page</a>. One inbox covers
        both apps.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .support {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0 6rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .back {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .back:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .kicker {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  article {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  em {
    color: var(--text);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-dim);
  }
</style>
